  "prompt": "How do you remember which continents are located in the northern hemisphere?",
  "response": "To remember which continents are located in the Northern Hemisphere, you can consider the following:\n\n1. **North America** - Entirely in the Northern Hemisphere.\n2. **Europe** - Entirely in the Northern Hemisphere.\n3. **Asia** - Mostly in the Northern Hemisphere, with only a small portion in the Southern Hemisphere.\n4. **Africa** - Straddles the equator, but the majority of the continent is in the Northern Hemisphere.\n\nA simple mnemonic to remember these could be \"NEAA,\" representing North America, Europe, and most of Asia and Africa. Additionally, think of continents that primarily lie above the equator or have large land masses north of it. This visualization can help clarify which continents are in the Northern Hemisphere.",
